  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Maria Weston Chapman begins this letter with a discussion of letters and family news. She says that &quot;Sam Sewall is so quiet he gets no abuse from anybody.&quot; She is willing to see Caroline Weston made head of an unnamed society. She mentions various abolitionists, including Wendell Phillips and Samuel May, and a circular that will be sent out to the Unitarians.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This letter is written on the verso and blank spaces of a form (document) for &quot;Anti-Slavery Peace Pledge&quot; and &quot;Disunion Pledge.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
